-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_id,
        return_date,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY 
                CASE WHEN status = 'approved' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END,
                return_id
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT item_id
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- int_items_with_category.sql
```sql
-- Join order items with products and categories, handle missing categories
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        oi.unit_price,
        COALESCE(c.category_name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        dr.return_id IS NOT NULL AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} dr
        ON dr.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    order_id,
    product_id,
    quantity,
    unit_price,
    category_name,
    is_returned
FROM source
```

-- fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Final fact table: product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        category_name,
        SUM(CASE WHEN is_returned THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
        COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_category') }}
    GROUP BY category_name
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    total_items_returned * 1.0 / total_items_sold AS return_rate
FROM source
ORDER BY category_name
